What's funny about the liberal-conservative argument is that they both rally around the Constitution while insisting the other doesn't.  *shrug* The Constitution is not outdated... like horoscopes, it is written in a vague enough manner so that the same precepts can be used to argue widely differing viewpoints - a Good Thing - and has a built in mechanism for self-correction should parts ever become outdated.  Never a question as to the document's worth.<br>
<br>
